node.text:
With the season in sight, we wanted to share a quick refresher on Priority Reservation Days vs. Week-Of Reservation Days

• Priority Reservation Days: On Nov. 6, you will be able to make reservations for the core season (Dec. 8 – April 4) across all of our resorts. As a pass holder, you can lock in up to 7 Priority Reservation Days for the core season in advance, and as many week-of reservations during the season as your pass type and availability allow.

•Week-Of Reservation Days: As our resorts start to open for the season, you can also take advantage of exclusive early season access by making week-of reservations. Booking a week-of reservation does not count against your Priority Reservation Days for the core season.  

Take a sneak peek of our new reservation system at the video above.

node.text:
Introducing the first-ever, limited-edition @HellyHansen Vail Lifaloft Jacket, designed around Vail’s heritage of the 10th Mtn Division & Legendary Back Bowls, equipped with a 2019-20 Epic Pass and exclusive Vail experiences. 
With only 100 total men’s and 100 total women’s jackets being produced, this tribute to Vail Mountain will be released this fall and sold exclusively in four select retailers across North America. 
For more details on the jacket and each city’s release, visit the link in our bio!

node.title: Vail x Helly Hansen | Meet the Vail LifaLoft Jacket

node.text: This past weekend served up some great views! Who's joining us this coming week? ☀️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 18, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: Some of the best summer days consist of riding up on the gondola and rolling down on a bike. Learn more about bike haul via the summer operations link in our bio!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: Mountain top yoga is back! Flow with us every Friday at 10 am from now until September 3rd. Conveniently located at the top of Gondola One, tickets are available at the Vail Village ticket office and are just $45, including scenic lift access, water, and a yoga mat to use during the class.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 14, 2021. May be an image of mountain and nature.

node.text: Winter will be here before we know it, and that means it’s time to start planning those vacations. Book by 7/31 to get the greatest savings on lodging this season with rates starting at $159! Visit the link in our bio to learn more.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 12, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and outdoors.

node.text: Who's ready to jump into a new week? Click the summer operations link in our bio to book your bungee trampoline tickets today!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 11, 2021. May be an image of tree and mountain.

node.text: Whether you choose to hike in or be whisked up to 10,000 feet by a gondola, the views from Eagle's Nest are well worth the adventure to get there. Explore the decks at all of our CO resorts via our Epic Road Trip highlight!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 11, 2021. May be an image of tree and mountain.

node.text: Mountain views at Vail never disappoint.🏔

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 07, 2021. May be an image of snow, mountain, tree and nature.

node.text: We've got winter on our mind today! Raise your hand if you can't wait for next season. ✋

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 03, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: ICYMI: Wildwood Grill is now serving all your favorite BBQ dishes from Express Lift, located in the base area near Gondola One. Grab some wings, ribs, or pulled pork and take in the views from the deck!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 02, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, child, people standing and sunglasses.

node.text: The Vail America Days Fourth of July Celebration is happening this Sunday, July 4th! Learn more about this year's event via the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on July 01, 2021. May be an image of tree and nature.

node.text: We've got great weather in the forecast for the holiday weekend. If you're planning on joining us, we encourage you to book Epic Discovery activities ahead of time! Plan your visit via the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vail Mountain on June 28, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: You never know who you're going to stroll into when you are hiking at Vail Mountain. We love our wildlife, but make sure to observe them from a distance!
